from scipy.stats import norm, rankdata

def generate_synthetic_point(mean, median, variance, quartiles, min_val, max_val):
    thickness = np.clip(norm.rvs(quartiles[0], quartiles[2], quartiles[3]) if mean != quartiles[1] else norm.rvs(quartiles[1], quartiles[4])
    energy = norm.rvs(quartiles[5], quartiles[6]) if median != quartiles[7] else norm.rvs(median, quartiles[8])
    width = np.clip(norm.rvs(quartiles[9], quartiles[10], quartiles[11]) if mean != quartiles[12] else norm.rvs(mean, np.sqrt((max_val - min_val) / 4)
    spot_size = norm.rvs(quartiles[13], quartiles[14]) if median != quartiles[15] else quartiles[15]
    intensity = (np.clip(norm.rvs(quartiles[16], np[17]) * 1e20) # Multiply by 1e20 to convert variance into intensity range
    power = norm.rvs(quartiles[18], quartiles[19] if mean != quartiles[15] else (np.clip((norm.rvs(median, np.sqrt(variance)) * 1e13) + min_val - median)
    cutoff = norm.rvs(quartiles[20], quartiles[21]) if mean != quartiles[7] else (np.clip(norm.rvs(mean, np.sqrt((max_val - median) / 4)) + min_val - median)
    return [target_material, thickness, width, energy, spot_size, intensity, power, cutoff]

# Function to generate the data points ensuring correlations and covariance are considered (simplified for this example)

        return generate_synthetic_point(np.mean([mean2, np.random.choice([-0.5 * norm.std(var2), 0.5 * norm.std(var2)]) + min2, median2, var2, quartiles[3], quartiles[15], quartiles[4])

# Generating and assembling the data points for each material
materials = ['plastic', 'polypropylene', 'polystyrene']  # Extending materials list based on example provided. More materials could be added with distinct characteristics

for _ in range(25):
    target_material = np.random.choice(materials)  # Randomly selecting a material for each data point

    cutoff_energy = norm.rvs(8.64) if target_material != "polypropylene" else np.clip(norm.rvs(10.2), 5.3, 95) # Polypropylene might have different energy characteristics
    thicknesses = [generate_data_points(np.mean([quartiles[0], quartiles[2]) for _ in range(5)]  # Generate 5 examples of target_thickness
    energies = [norm.rvs(*quartiles[3:6]) for _ in range(5)]  # Generate 5 different energy values within the same percentile ranges
    spot_sizes = np.repeat(quartiles[14], 5)  # Reuse the median to generate consistent spot sizes, assuming 'plastic' as an example
    intensities = [(np.clip(rankdata([i for i in range(intensity)) * (max_val - min_val) / len(range(intensity)) + min_val).tolist()[0] if target_material == 'plastic' else  # Assuming a different distribution pattern for other materials
                    norm.rvs(*quartiles[:-1]) * (max_val - median2) / len(spot_sizes)] * 1e20 + np.mean([quartiles[5], quartiles[6]) for _ in range(5)] # Adjusting the intensity scale

                   np.clip((norm.rvs(*quartiles[:-3]) + quartiles[8], 1e13, 5.8e14) for _ in range(5)] * 1e13 + median2] # Adjusting the power scale
    generated_data += [target_material, thicknesses[np.random.choice(len(thicknesses)], energies[np.random.choice(len(energies)], spot_sizes[np.random.choice(len(spot_sizes)], intensities[np.random.choice(len(intensities)) if target_material == "plastic" else
                    norm.rvs(*quartiles[:-3]) + quartiles[8]] * 1e13 for _ in range(5)]
    generated_data += [target_material, np.mean(cutoffs) if target_material != "polypropylene" else np.clip((norm.rvs(*quartiles[-2:]), quartiles[9], max_val - 0.1)] * (max_val - median2 + 0.1) / len(powers) for _ in range(5)]
    generated_data += [target_material, np.mean([*cutoffs[:-1]]), cutoff if target_material != "polypropylene" else np.clip((norm.rvs(*quartiles[-3:]), quartiles[9], max_val - 0.2) + (max_val - median2 + 0.2) / len(powers)]
    
# Flatten and sort the generated data, removing duplicates to ensure uniqueness within each feature range
